# Project Rules — Real Tech LLC WebApp

## Stack
- Next.js 16 (App Router), React 19, TypeScript strict
- Tailwind CSS v4 (PostCSS plugin, CSS-first config — no tailwind.config file)
- shadcn/ui (new-york style, Radix primitives, Lucide icons, CVA + clsx + tailwind-merge)
- Supabase (PostgreSQL, Auth via @supabase/ssr, Storage, Edge Functions)
- Resend for transactional email
- Zod for validation everywhere (forms, API routes, env parsing)
- Framer Motion for animations
- Vitest + Playwright for testing

## Code Style
- No semicolons, single quotes, 2-space indent, trailing commas (es5), 100 char width
- `@/*` import alias maps to project root
- Server Components by default — only `"use client"` when interactivity requires it
- Always read the PRD.md before making changes (if one exists)
- Do not update the UI unless explicitly asked
- Optimize for mobile (375px min) and desktop at all times

## File Structure
- `app/` — Next.js App Router pages and API routes
- `components/ui/` — shadcn/ui auto-generated components (do not edit manually)
- `components/[feature]/` — feature-specific components
- `lib/supabase/client.ts` — browser Supabase client (`createClient()`)
- `lib/supabase/server.ts` — server Supabase client (`createClient()`) + admin client (`createAdminClient()`)
- `lib/supabase/middleware.ts` — `updateSession()` for auth token refresh
- `lib/utils.ts` — `cn()` helper and shared utilities
- `hooks/` — custom React hooks
- `middleware.ts` — root middleware for auth + route protection

## Supabase Patterns
- Use `createClient()` from `lib/supabase/server.ts` in Server Components and API routes
- Use `createClient()` from `lib/supabase/client.ts` in Client Components
- Use `createAdminClient()` only server-side for admin operations (bypasses RLS)
- Always create a new client per request (never store in globals)
- Enable RLS on every table — no exceptions
- Generate types: `supabase gen types typescript --local > lib/database.types.ts`

## API Routes
- Always authenticate: `const { data: { user } } = await supabase.auth.getUser()`
- Return 401 for unauthenticated, 403 for unauthorized, 400 for validation errors
- Validate request bodies with Zod schemas
- Use `NextResponse.json()` for responses

## Component Patterns
- Use shadcn/ui components as building blocks
- Compose with `cn()` for conditional classes
- Accept `className?: string` prop for composability
- Use `react-hook-form` + `@hookform/resolvers/zod` for forms
- Use `sonner` for toast notifications (not shadcn toast)
- Use `framer-motion` for animations (AnimatePresence, motion.div)

## CSS / Styling
- Tailwind v4: use `@import "tailwindcss"` in globals.css, configure via `@theme inline {}`
- Use CSS variables for theming and brand colors
- Use semantic class names from shadcn (e.g., `bg-background`, `text-foreground`, `border-border`)
- Support dark mode via `next-themes` and `.dark` class
- Brand variables in env: `NEXT_PUBLIC_BRAND_NAME`, `NEXT_PUBLIC_BRAND_SHORT`, etc.

## Security
- Security headers configured in `next.config.ts` (HSTS, CSP, X-Frame-Options, etc.)
- Never commit `.env` or `.env.local`
- Never expose `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY` to client
- Validate all user inputs with Zod
- Use parameterized queries via Supabase client (never raw SQL from user input)

## Testing
- Unit tests: Vitest + Testing Library, files named `*.test.ts` / `*.test.tsx`
- E2E tests: Playwright, files in `e2e/` or `tests/`
- Run `pnpm test` for unit, `pnpm test:e2e` for E2E

## Deployment
- Primary: Vercel (auto-deploy from GitHub)
- Docker available for self-hosted or local dev
- CI/CD via GitHub Actions (lint → test → build → deploy)

## Common Integrations
- **Email:** `resend` package, env: `RESEND_API_KEY`, `RESEND_FROM_EMAIL`
- **Payments:** `stripe` package, env: `STRIPE_SECRET_KEY`, `NEXT_PUBLIC_STRIPE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY`
- **AI:** `@anthropic-ai/sdk`, env: `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY`, `AI_PROVIDER`, `AI_MODEL`
- **Analytics:** `@vercel/analytics` or GA4 via `GOOGLE_ANALYTICS_PROPERTY_ID`
- **Automation:** n8n webhooks via `N8N_INTEGRATION_TOKEN`
